Computer Configuration > Windows Settings > Security Settings > Local Policies > User Rights Assignment > Allow log on locally

Add:

grp-modelshopLAC (shared account group)

Admin groups if needed (e.g. DPT Admins)

This whitelists only the users/groups you explicitly permit.

3. Secure Remote Desktop (RDP) Access
a. Allow Logon via RDP
GPO Path:
Computer Configuration > Windows Settings > Security Settings > Local Policies > User Rights Assignment > Allow log on through Remote Desktop Services

Add:

grp-modelshopRDC

Admin accounts (if RDP is allowed for them)

b. Configure the Local Remote Desktop Users Group
Avoid populating this group manually on the device.

Use GPO preferences or Restricted Groups to manage this:

GPO Path:
Computer Configuration > Policies > Windows Settings > Security Settings > Restricted Groups

Set members of Remote Desktop Users to exactly match grp-modelshopRDC

4. Enforce via OU Targeting
Place all modelshop devices into a dedicated OU (e.g. OU=ModelshopDevices)

Link the GPO that applies login restrictions to this OU

This ensures device-scoped, consistent enforcement

5. Harden Local Accounts
Disable or rename local built-in Administrator

Ensure no local accounts remain enabled unless required for break-glass access

Audit via script:

